entries.femaleVariant: Just comes naturally to me.
Let's say I got bored pushing paper.
Left my clan, had to do something in Night City.
The streets are my home. Don't know any other.
Gets old, working a desk in perfectly climate-controlled conditions.
Wait, wait, wait. Tell me you worked for the post office, not a corp.
Arasaka.
You're kidding.
Long story. But our paths diverged, we parted amicably. Sort of.
I mean, respect. Johnny always said you only leave Arasaka feet first. Here you are, still kicking.
Yeah – sort of.
Sorry to disappoint, but there's no story. Just comes naturally to me.
Naturally modest, naturally blunt or boring as hell. Still can't decide which one you are.
Just worked out that way. Came to Night City, got my first job, then another... And so on, and so forth.
But before Night City? Where'd you roam?
With the nomads, Bakker family. But it fell apart. Now I go it alone.
Ah, now I get how we lost the cops so fast. You all, it's in your blood. Like you're one with your ride, huh?
Ehh... stereotypes, Ker. How many nomads you know, besides me?
Ey, hold up. I had my nomad BD phase. Fuckin' wild ride. Oh, and we had a stunt guy from some clan once, brought him on to do the "Born Stupid" video.
What I thought.
Came up on Night City's streets. Fixers find people like me pretty quick. Just snowballs from there.
Never thought about getting out?
If it ain't broke, why fix it?
So, how'd you get into this? This... I mean, you know...
entries.maleVariant: Speaking of anarchy. How'd you get into this? This... I mean, you know...

entries.femaleVariant: You're asking why I do what I do?
What'd you do after Samurai broke up?
Working on the new album?
How's ol' Kovachek?
Everything cool with Us Cracks?
How's Kovachek? Throw himself into the Del Coronado yet?
How's your manager, Kerry?
How's things with Us Cracks? Coming along?
entries.maleVariant: How's things with Us Cracks? Comin' along?

entries.femaleVariant: How's the Us Cracks thing? Died down?
[Kiss Kerry] How's things?
Our little taste of anarchy – I liked it.
So what'd you do after Samurai tanked?
Bet he went to go "find himself" on some shithole beach in the Philippines.
Took me a while to pick myself up. Spent two years out on Masbate. Went back to my roots.
What'd I say? High outta his mind all day, spent all night fucking anything that moved.
And? Help at all?
Heheh, in the end, yeah. Think the media got the rest of the story.
How's the new album? Coming along?
So, when can we expect the new Kerry Eurodyne album to drop?
Know what? Our little anarchic gesture back there – kinda liked it.
entries.maleVariant: Ya know what? Our little anarchic gesture back there – I kinda liked it.

entries.femaleVariant: Me too. Just hopin' the Us Cracks girls liked it less.
Touchy subject, V.
Got a few ideas in the works. Mostly scraps, though. We'll see what comes of 'em.
Little busy with more important things at the moment.
Like what?
Well... Drinkin', mostly. And procrastinating.
Mhm. Thinkin' 'bout calling it "Kerry Eurodyne." It's symbolic, y'know? A rebirth.
Let me have a listen?
Not yet – still too rough around the edges. But it's getting there!
I listen to the new tracks and... it's like I'm in a goddamn wax museum, lookin' at old me's.
Yeah. Why?
A little freaky, but still fuckin' awesome.
Yeah, just sent me a demo of theirs to check out.
Y'know, that'll never be my world. But hey, I'm happy to add a little blood 'n' chrome to their fakepop slice 'n' dice.
One thing, and one thing only – don't ever mention those talentless hacks in front of me again.
entries.maleVariant: V, don't be a dick. Don't mention those talentless hacks in front of me again.

entries.femaleVariant: OK, OK, never said a word.
Heh, he will. I'm done with that dickwipe. Cuttin' that contract, tossin' him out with the trash, even if I gotta throw a few extra eds his way.
Or, wait, lemme rephrase – Kovachek still your manager?
entries.maleVariant: Or, wait, lemme rephrase – 's Kovachek still your manager?

entries.femaleVariant: Don't worry about him. Got an idea. Lettin' it simmer.
What happens then, we'll see.
Hah! What I like to hear.
Catch you later!
